This paper is about natural language generation from Abstract Meaning Representation (AMR), which is a subfield of computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method using a metric related to information retrieval, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
